cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on learning universal distributed representations of sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an unsupervised method for learning these representations, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses consistency constraints on sequences of tokens, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories that deal with sequence modeling and image processing. Finally, the paper uses a multitask setting and an ensemble of encoders, which could be related to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category that deals with neural networks and optimization.
